        <div1 type="summary">
            <p><add hand="#barker">Deposition concerning loss of $20.</add></p>
        </div1>
        <div1 type="body">
            

<p><date when="1825-04-06">This day</date> personally appeared before me <persName>Stephen F. Austin Judge</persName>
of this <placeName>Jurisdiction </placeName><persName>James Small</persName> who being sworn deposeth and
testi[fí]eth that he was in possession of a certain certificate a <placeName>land
office</placeName> bill drawn in favor of <persName>Oliver Jones</persName> by <persName>Sam M Williams</persName> in
behalf of the <persName>Empresario Austin</persName> for twenty dollars, which bill was
washed to pieces in the pocket of his clothes and entirely destroyed,
further deposes he has never recd value for the same or any part
thereof.</p>

<p><placeName>San Felipe de Austin</placeName> <date when="1826-04-06">6th April 1826</date>.</p>
<p><persName>James Small  </persName>  [Rubric]</p>
<p>Sworn to before me</p>

<p><persName>S. F. Austin</persName>    [Rubric]</p>

<p>[On reverse] Recd of <persName>S. F. Austin</persName> a receipt for twenty dollars in
place of the within described that was lost.</p>

<p><persName>James Small</persName>    [Rubric]</p>
<p>[On margin] <persName>James Small</persName> receipt</p>



        </div1>
